File: Pastor Omotoso at the Port Elizabeth High Court. PORT ELIZABETH - Nigerian televangelist Timothy Omotoso is back in the Port Elizabeth High Court to apply for leave to appeal against his bail denial.    His third bid was denied on Wednesday. READ: Omotoso to stay behind bars The charismatic pastor was arrested in 2017. He faces almost 100 charges, including human trafficking and rape. The state believes he's a flight risk and may evade trial. Omotoso's family accuses the courts of being biased and robbing the pastor of his freedom.